    "content": "Sinew harvested from a @[suneater owlbear's](species:2c7aef12-0a0f-4945-841f-c8de155573db)Â spine can imbue arrows with low-level radiation, which is passed onto a target when struck by the ammunition. The magic of suneater respiration lies in their photometabolism; they can convert sunlight into pure, concentrated radiant energy, unleashing unholy beams of destructive force.\r\n\r\nThe wielder gains a +3 bonus to attack and damage rolls made with this magic weapon.\r\n\r\n[i]Sunshot. [/i]While in sunlight, this bow doesn't need ammunition. If you draw this weapon's bowstring without nocking an arrow, it produces its own ammunition, automatically creating a radiant arrow when you make a ranged attack with it. The attack deals radiant damage instead of the weapon's normal damage. The arrow created by this weapon vanishes the instant after it hits or misses a target.\r\n\r\n[i]Irradiation. [/i]A creature that takes radiant damage from this bow becomes magically marked for [b]1 hour[/b]. During this time, it leaves an invisble trail that can be seen by creatures with truesight or creatures using the [i]detect magic [/i]spell. The trail fades after 1 hour.\r\n\r\nWhen attuned to the weapon, you gain the Solar Beam and Daylight property and has [b]3 charges. [/b]The bow regains [b]1 [/b]expended charge daily at dawn. If it is exposed to dawn's light, it regains [b]all [/b]expended charges instead.\r\n\r\n[i]Solar Beam. [/i]As an action, you can expend [b]1 charge[/b] to fire a beam of solar energy in a [b]5-foot-wide, 60-foot-long line [/b]originating from you. Each creature in the area must make a [b]DC 16 Dexterity saving throw[/b], taking 6d8 radiant damage on a failed save, or half as much damage on a successful one.\r\n\r\n[i]Daylight. [/i]When you take the Attack action, you can use one attack to fire a radiant arrow from this bow at a surface within the bow's range and expend [b]1 charge[/b]. A magical effect identical to the [i]daylight [/i]spell manifests for [b]1 hour[/b], centred wherever the arrow strikes the surface.",
